# GitHub Linguist overrides
#
# The report template is a pre-built React bundle inherited from the JS
# project's @midscene/visualizer — a single ~1600-line minified HTML file
# that inlines large amounts of JS/CSS plus a WASM blob. Its size skews
# the repo's "Languages" breakdown (HTML ≫ Python) even though this is a
# Python library. Mark the whole report_template/ as vendored so Linguist
# excludes it from language statistics while keeping the files visible
# in diffs and PRs.

pymidscene/resources/report_template/** linguist-vendored

# Keep the bundled report template as-is — no CRLF/LF auto-conversion.
pymidscene/resources/report_template/report.html -text
